item.title: About Arnav
item.description: Hello! My name is Arnav, and I’m a second-year Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE) student at the University of Toronto. I’m interested in learning about and working in computer hardware and machine intelligence. Outside of classes, I’m involved with the University of Toronto Engineering Society (EngSoc) and the IEEE University of Toronto Student Branch (IEEE UofT). Feel free to reach out, I’m always looking to connect! LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/arnavpatil/

item.title: Class Notes
item.description: On this page, I’ve curated a collection of my course notes. These course notes are mainly final exam review or transcribed textbook or lecture notes. While none of these notes packages are full representations of the course, I found them incredibly helpful in preparation for assessments. Unfortunately, there’s some courses, especially in Fall semester of my first year, where I didn’t take notes or the notes were provided by the instructor.
